# SPA Navigation & URL Sync

Policy for keeping the **address bar** aligned with what the user sees. Applies to all Preact client work.

## Principle

| Layer | Role |
|-------|------|
| **URL** (path + query) | Canonical, shareable, reloadable view |
| **Router props** | `chapterId`, path params from `preact-router` |
| **`history.state`** | Ephemeral hints only — never chapter text, lists, or large payloads (~640KB limit) |
| **API / localStorage** | Scroll position, drafts, preferences when not shareable |

**Address-bar drift:** UI shows view A but URL shows view B → broken F5, share, and Back. Fix by syncing shareable state to the URL on every navigation path.

## Stack

- Router: `preact-router` in `@src/client/AppRouter.tsx`
- Prefer `route(url)` and `route(url, true)` over raw `history.pushState` / `replaceState` so `Router onChange` fires and analytics (`arcane:route-change`) stay correct
- Route map SSOT: `@.cursor/rules/routing.mdc`

## push vs replace

| User action | API | Example |
|-------------|-----|---------|
| Navigate to a distinct view | `route(url)` — **push** | Reading: next chapter |
| Canonicalize entry URL (no extra history entry) | `route(url, true)` — **replace** | `/projects/:id/reading` → first chapter |
| Refine current view in place | `route(url, true)` or `history.replaceState` | Catalog filter chips; debug filters |

Use **push** when the user expects Back to undo (chapter, page, tab as route). Use **replace** for in-place refinements or one-shot redirects.

## Path vs query

| Use path segment | Use query param |
|------------------|-----------------|
| Entity identity (`:chapterId`, `:projectId`) | Filters (`filter`, `author`, `tag`) |
| Distinct routes in sitemap / SEO | Search prefill (`search`) |
| Reading / editing contexts | Scroll target (`paragraph`) |

Add new path segments to `routing.mdc`, `AppRouter.tsx`, and server SPA fallback in the same PR.

## Implementation recipe

1. **Decide** if state is shareable (another person should reproduce the view from a link).
2. **Add** `buildXxxUrl()` in `src/client/utils/` (see `@src/client/utils/readingRoutes.ts`, `buildCatalogUrl` in `HomePage.tsx`).
3. **On every mutation** (button, keyboard, TOC): save side effects first (e.g. reading position), then `route(url)` with guard:

   ```typescript
   if (window.location.pathname !== url) route(url);
   ```

4. **Derive UI** from URL: router props (`chapterId`) or `URLSearchParams` on mount; re-sync on `popstate` and/or `arcane:route-change`.
5. **Optional optimistic local state** for instant UI; URL remains source of truth (see `lastInitialChapterIdRef` in `ReadingMode`).
6. **Avoid full-page spinner** when only a route param changes — fetch page-level data once per mount (see `PublicationReadingPage` `progressLoaded`).

## Back / Forward

- `preact-router` updates props on `popstate`; child reads `initialChapterId` / query and syncs index
- Reset ephemeral guards when URL identity changes (e.g. `hasAppliedInitialScrollRef` on `initialChapterId` change)
- Do not call `route()` again when reacting to Back — URL already changed

## Do not sync to URL

- Modal open/closed (glossary, settings, share dialog)
- Scroll offset within a view (unless explicit product requirement)
- Unsaved form drafts
- Transient loading / error flags

**Exception:** authenticated reading position uses `PATCH /api/publications/:id/reading-position`, not URL.

## Reference implementations

| Feature | Files | Pattern |
|---------|-------|---------|
| Shared URL hook | `hooks/useUrlSync.ts`, `utils/catalogRoutes.ts` | `useUrlSync` + route builders in `utils/` |
| Profile tabs | `ProfilePage.tsx`, `profileRoutes.ts` | `useUrlSync` push |
| Publication filters | `PublicationPage.tsx`, `publicationRoutes.ts` | `useUrlSyncListeners` + debounced replace |
| Project search | `ProjectPage.tsx`, `projectRoutes.ts` | `?search=` opens modal; chapter `?search=&paragraph=` |
| Reading chapters | `ReadingMode/index.tsx`, `readingRoutes.ts` | Path push; `?paragraph=N` for guest scroll |
| Catalog filters | `HomePage.tsx`, `catalogRoutes.ts` | `useUrlSync` push |
| Chapter editor | `ChapterPage.tsx`, `projectRoutes.ts` | Path + `?search=`, `?paragraph=` (UUID) |
| Admin tabs | `AppRouter.tsx` | Separate paths per section |
| Debug filters | `debug-app/hooks/useUrlSync.ts` | Query + `replaceState` (dev only) |

